snippet: At Senator Tom Harkin’s annual steak fry fund-raiser, Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. might have unofficially kicked off a third presidential campaign, but Iowans are reluctant to support a bid.
abstract: Political Memo; Vice Pres Joseph R Biden, delivering keynote speech at Iowa fundraiser for Sen Tom Harkin, may have unofficially kicked off his third presidential campaign, but Iowans remain reluctant to support his bid; early polling data nationwide suggests that Democrats, who profess fondness for Biden, are not willing to support his presidential hopes.
lead_paragraph: At Senator Tom Harkin’s annual steak fry fund-raiser, Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. might have unofficially kicked off a third presidential campaign, but Iowans are reluctant to support a bid.

headline.main: Finding Love in Iowa, but Maybe Not Votes
headline.print_headline: Finding Love in Iowa, But Maybe Not Votes
